parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the trailer, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
Valve stem failure can cause loss of tire pressure, leading to tire failure, loss of control, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.

The failure of the structural frame, including the crossmember and main beam, can cause the vehicle to lose stability and control, leading to accidents or injuries. Additionally, the failure of the metal-welded tubing can lead to a loss of structural integrity, compromising the safety of the vehicle and its occupants.
symptoms: The rear of the vehicle moves up and down violently while driving over bumps
and the vehicle's structural integrity is compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective RV Frame and Axle Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective frame and axle assembly can cause the RV to become detached from the tow vehicle while in motion, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The step deck box and king pin box metal rip or fail
causing the RV to become unstable and potentially detach from the tow vehicle
resulting in loss of control and potential accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked frame of the pin hitch can cause the hitch to fail, leading to loss of control of the trailer, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Unusual clanging or rattling sounds while towing
hitch is too close to the bed of the truck
visible cracks in the frame of the pin hitch
buckled or pushed-up closet or interior walls of the trailer.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lippert Components 5th Wheel Hitch Pin Box Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 5th wheel hitch pin box can cause the trailer to detach from the tow vehicle, leading to accidents, property damage, injury, and possible death.
symptoms: Cracks in the front and rear cross members that support the 5th wheel hitch
failure of the 5th wheel hitch pin box to weld to the frame cross members

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The weakness in the design of the 5th wheel hitch on Lippert Components frames can cause the hitch to fail, leading to accidents, property damage, injury, and possible death.
symptoms: Cracks in the front and rear cross members that support the 5th wheel hitch
failure of the 5th wheel hitch pin box to weld to the frame cross members
